{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"I've actually been waiting by the phone"},{"time":3000,"text":"for a call from TED for years."},{"time":6000,"text":"And in fact, in 2000, I was ready to talk about eBay, but no call."},{"time":12000,"text":"In 2003, I was ready to do a talk"},{"time":15000,"text":"about the Skoll Foundation and social entrepreneurship. No call."},{"time":22000,"text":"In 2004, I started Participant Productions"},{"time":24000,"text":"and we had a really good first year, and no call."},{"time":27000,"text":"And finally, I get a call last year,"},{"time":31000,"text":"and then I have to go up after J.J. Abrams."},{"time":33000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":36000,"text":"You've got a cruel sense of humor, TED."},{"time":37000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":39000,"text":"When I first moved to Hollywood from Silicon Valley,"},{"time":43000,"text":"I had some misgivings."},{"time":44000,"text":"But I found that there were some advantages to being in Hollywood."},{"time":48000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":49000,"text":"And, in fact, some advantages to owning your own media company."},{"time":56000,"text":"And I also found that Hollywood and Silicon Valley"},{"time":58000,"text":"have a lot more in common than I would have dreamed."},{"time":61000,"text":"Hollywood has its sex symbols, and the Valley has its sex symbols."},{"time":64000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":66000,"text":"Hollywood has its rivalries, and the Valley has its rivalries."},{"time":70000,"text":"Hollywood gathers around power tables,"},{"time":72000,"text":"and the Valley gathers around power tables."},{"time":74000,"text":"So it turned out there was a lot more in common"},{"time":76000,"text":"than I would have dreamed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":78000,"text":"But I'm actually here today to tell a story."},{"time":81000,"text":"And part of it is a personal story. When Chris invited me to speak,"},{"time":86000,"text":"he said, people think of you as a bit of an enigma,"},{"time":88000,"text":"and they want to know what drives you a bit."},{"time":91000,"text":"And what really drives me is a vision of the future"},{"time":94000,"text":"that I think we all share."},{"time":95000,"text":"It's a world of peace and prosperity and sustainability."},{"time":99000,"text":"And when we heard a lot of the presentations"},{"time":104000,"text":"over the last couple of days,"},{"time":105000,"text":"Ed Wilson and the pictures of James Nachtwey,"},{"time":109000,"text":"I think we all realized how far we have to go"},{"time":111000,"text":"to get to this new version of humanity"},{"time":112000,"text":"that I like to call \"Humanity 2.0.\""},{"time":115000,"text":"And it's also something that resides in each of us,"},{"time":120000,"text":"to close what I think"},{"time":121000,"text":"are the two big calamities in the world today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":125000,"text":"One is the gap in opportunity --"},{"time":128000,"text":"this gap that President Clinton last night"},{"time":131000,"text":"called uneven, unfair and unsustainable --"},{"time":134000,"text":"and, out of that, comes poverty and illiteracy and disease"},{"time":137000,"text":"and all these evils that we see around us."},{"time":140000,"text":"But perhaps the other, bigger gap is what we call the hope gap."},{"time":145000,"text":"And someone, at some point, came up with this very bad idea"},{"time":148000,"text":"that an ordinary individual couldn't make a difference in the world."},{"time":152000,"text":"And I think that's just a horrible thing."},{"time":154000,"text":"And so chapter one really begins today, with all of us,"},{"time":158000,"text":"because within each of us is the power to"},{"time":162000,"text":"equal those opportunity gaps and to close the hope gaps."},{"time":165000,"text":"And if the men and women of TED"},{"time":167000,"text":"can't make a difference in the world, I don't know who can."}]},{"cues":[{"time":170000,"text":"And for me, a lot of this started when I was younger"},{"time":173000,"text":"and my family used to go camping in upstate New York."},{"time":177000,"text":"And there really wasn't much to do there for the summer,"},{"time":179000,"text":"except get beaten up by my sister or read books."},{"time":183000,"text":"And so I used to read authors like James Michener"},{"time":186000,"text":"and James Clavell and Ayn Rand."},{"time":188000,"text":"And their stories made the world seem a very small"},{"time":192000,"text":"and interconnected place."},{"time":194000,"text":"And it struck me that if I could write stories"},{"time":198000,"text":"that were about this world as being small and interconnected,"},{"time":200000,"text":"that maybe I could get people interested in the issues"},{"time":204000,"text":"that affected us all, and maybe engage them to make a difference."}]},{"cues":[{"time":208000,"text":"I didn't think that was necessarily the best way to make a living,"},{"time":212000,"text":"so I decided to go on a path to become financially independent,"},{"time":216000,"text":"so I could write these stories as quickly as I could."},{"time":220000,"text":"I then had a bit of a wake-up call when I was 14."},{"time":223000,"text":"And my dad came home one day"},{"time":225000,"text":"and announced that he had cancer, and it looked pretty bad."},{"time":229000,"text":"And what he said was, he wasn't so much afraid that he might die,"},{"time":233000,"text":"but that he hadn't done the things that he wanted to with his life."},{"time":238000,"text":"And knock on wood, he's still alive today, many years later."},{"time":242000,"text":"But for a young man that made a real impression on me,"},{"time":245000,"text":"that one never knows how much time one really has."},{"time":248000,"text":"So I set out in a hurry. I studied engineering."},{"time":253000,"text":"I started a couple of businesses"},{"time":255000,"text":"that I thought would be the ticket to financial freedom."}]},{"cues":[{"time":258000,"text":"One of those businesses was a computer rental business"},{"time":261000,"text":"called Micros on the Move,"},{"time":262000,"text":"which is very well named,"},{"time":263000,"text":"because people kept stealing the computers."},{"time":265000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":266000,"text":"So I figured I needed to learn a little bit more about business,"},{"time":270000,"text":"so I went to Stanford Business School and studied there."},{"time":273000,"text":"And while I was there, I made friends with a fellow"},{"time":276000,"text":"named Pierre Omidyar, who is here today. And Pierre, I apologize"},{"time":279000,"text":"for this. This is a photo from the old days."},{"time":282000,"text":"And just after I'd graduated, Pierre came to me"},{"time":284000,"text":"with this idea to help people"},{"time":286000,"text":"buy and sell things online with each other."},{"time":288000,"text":"And with the wisdom of my Stanford degree,"},{"time":290000,"text":"I said, \"Pierre, what a stupid idea.\""},{"time":292000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":293000,"text":"And needless to say, I was right."},{"time":294000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":296000,"text":"But right after that, Pierre -- in '96, Pierre and I left our full-time jobs"},{"time":300000,"text":"to build eBay as a company. And the rest of that story, you know."},{"time":305000,"text":"The company went public two years later"},{"time":307000,"text":"and is today one of the best known companies in the world."},{"time":310000,"text":"Hundreds of millions of people use it in hundreds of countries, and so on."},{"time":314000,"text":"But for me, personally, it was a real change."},{"time":318000,"text":"I went from living in a house with five guys in Palo Alto"},{"time":322000,"text":"and living off their leftovers,"},{"time":323000,"text":"to all of a sudden having all kinds of resources."},{"time":327000,"text":"And I wanted to figure out how I could"},{"time":329000,"text":"take the blessing of these resources and share it with the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":333000,"text":"And around that time, I met John Gardner,"},{"time":336000,"text":"who is a remarkable man."},{"time":338000,"text":"He was the architect of the Great Society programs"},{"time":342000,"text":"under Lyndon Johnson in the 1960s."},{"time":344000,"text":"And I asked him what he felt was the best thing I could do,"},{"time":347000,"text":"or anyone could do, to make a difference"},{"time":349000,"text":"in the long-term issues facing humanity."},{"time":353000,"text":"And John said, \"Bet on good people doing good things."},{"time":357000,"text":"Bet on good people doing good things.\""},{"time":359000,"text":"And that really resonated with me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":361000,"text":"I started a foundation"},{"time":363000,"text":"to bet on these good people doing good things."},{"time":365000,"text":"These leading, innovative, nonprofit folks,"},{"time":368000,"text":"who are using business skills in a very leveraged way"},{"time":371000,"text":"to solve social problems."},{"time":373000,"text":"People today we call social entrepreneurs."},{"time":376000,"text":"And to put a face on it, people like Muhammad Yunus,"},{"time":378000,"text":"who started the Grameen Bank,"},{"time":380000,"text":"has lifted 100 million people plus out of poverty around the world,"},{"time":384000,"text":"won the Nobel Peace Prize."},{"time":385000,"text":"But there's also a lot of people that you don't know."},{"time":388000,"text":"Folks like Ann Cotton, who started a group called CAMFED in Africa,"},{"time":392000,"text":"because she felt girls' education was lagging."},{"time":395000,"text":"And she started it about 10 years ago,"},{"time":397000,"text":"and today, she educates over a quarter million African girls."},{"time":402000,"text":"And somebody like Dr. Victoria Hale,"},{"time":405000,"text":"who started the world's first nonprofit pharmaceutical company,"},{"time":408000,"text":"and whose first drug will be fighting visceral leishmaniasis,"},{"time":414000,"text":"also known as black fever."},{"time":416000,"text":"And by 2010, she hopes to eliminate this disease,"},{"time":419000,"text":"which is really a scourge in the developing world."},{"time":422000,"text":"And so this is one way to bet"},{"time":424000,"text":"on good people doing good things."}]},{"cues":[{"time":425000,"text":"And a lot of this comes together in a philosophy of change"},{"time":429000,"text":"that I find really is powerful."},{"time":433000,"text":"It's what we call, \"Invest, connect and celebrate.\""},{"time":435000,"text":"And invest: if you see good people doing good things,"},{"time":438000,"text":"invest in them. Invest in their organizations,"},{"time":440000,"text":"or in business. Invest in these folks."},{"time":443000,"text":"Connecting them together through conferences --"},{"time":445000,"text":"like a TED -- brings so many powerful connections,"},{"time":448000,"text":"or through the World Forum on Social Entrepreneurship"},{"time":451000,"text":"that my foundation does at Oxford every year."},{"time":454000,"text":"And celebrate them: tell their stories,"},{"time":457000,"text":"because not only are there good people doing good work,"},{"time":459000,"text":"but their stories can help close these gaps of hope."}]},{"cues":[{"time":464000,"text":"And it was this last part of the mission, the celebrate part,"},{"time":467000,"text":"that really got me back to thinking when I was a kid"},{"time":471000,"text":"and wanted to tell stories to get people involved"},{"time":473000,"text":"in the issues that affect us all."},{"time":475000,"text":"And a light bulb went off,"},{"time":477000,"text":"which was, first, that I didn't actually have to do the writing myself, I could find writers."},{"time":482000,"text":"And then the next light bulb was, better than just writing,"},{"time":485000,"text":"what about film and TV, to get out to people in a big way?"},{"time":489000,"text":"And I thought about the films that inspired me,"},{"time":491000,"text":"films like \"Gandhi\" and \"Schindler's List.\""},{"time":494000,"text":"And I wondered who was doing these kinds of films today."},{"time":497000,"text":"And there really wasn't a specific company"},{"time":500000,"text":"that was focused on the public interest."}]},{"cues":[{"time":503000,"text":"So, in 2003, I started to make my way around Los Angeles"},{"time":508000,"text":"to talk about the idea of a pro-social media company"},{"time":511000,"text":"and I was met with a lot of encouragement."},{"time":514000,"text":"One of the lines of encouragement"},{"time":517000,"text":"that I heard over and over was,"},{"time":519000,"text":"\"The streets of Hollywood are littered with the carcasses of people like you,"},{"time":523000,"text":"who think you're going to come to this town and make movies.\""},{"time":526000,"text":"And then of course, there was the other adage."},{"time":528000,"text":"\"The surest way to become a millionaire"},{"time":530000,"text":"is to start by being a billionaire and go into the movie business.\""},{"time":533000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":535000,"text":"Undeterred, in January of 2004, I started Participant Productions"},{"time":540000,"text":"with the vision to be a global media company"},{"time":543000,"text":"focused on the public interest."},{"time":545000,"text":"And our mission is to produce entertainment"},{"time":547000,"text":"that creates and inspires social change."},{"time":549000,"text":"And we don't just want people to see our movies"},{"time":552000,"text":"and say, that was fun, and forget about it."},{"time":554000,"text":"We want them to actually get involved in the issues."},{"time":557000,"text":"In 2005, we launched our first slate of films,"},{"time":560000,"text":"\"Murder Ball,\" \"North Country,\" \"Syriana\""},{"time":563000,"text":"and \"Good Night and Good Luck.\""},{"time":564000,"text":"And much to my surprise, they were noticed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":567000,"text":"We ended up with 11 Oscar nominations for these films."},{"time":571000,"text":"And it turned out to be a pretty good year for this guy."},{"time":574000,"text":"Perhaps more importantly,"},{"time":575000,"text":"tens of thousands of people joined the advocacy programs"},{"time":579000,"text":"and the activism programs"},{"time":581000,"text":"that we created to go around the movies."},{"time":583000,"text":"And we had an online component of that,"},{"time":586000,"text":"our community sect called Participate.net."},{"time":588000,"text":"But with our social sector partners, like the ACLU and PBS and the"},{"time":593000,"text":"Sierra Club and the NRDC, once people saw the film,"},{"time":596000,"text":"there was actually something they could do to make a difference."}]},{"cues":[{"time":600000,"text":"One of these films in particular, called \"North Country,\" was actually"},{"time":606000,"text":"kind of a box office disaster."},{"time":608000,"text":"But it was a film that starred Charlize Theron"},{"time":611000,"text":"and it was about women's rights, women's empowerment,"},{"time":614000,"text":"domestic violence and so on."},{"time":616000,"text":"And we released the film at the same time that"},{"time":619000,"text":"the Congress was debating the renewal of the Violence Against Women Act."},{"time":624000,"text":"And with screenings on the Hill, and discussions,"},{"time":627000,"text":"and with our social sector partners,"},{"time":629000,"text":"like the National Organization of Women,"},{"time":632000,"text":"the film was widely credited"},{"time":634000,"text":"with influencing the successful renewal of the act."},{"time":638000,"text":"And that to me, spoke volumes, because it's --"},{"time":642000,"text":"the film started about a true-life story"},{"time":644000,"text":"about a woman who was harassed, sued her employer,"},{"time":648000,"text":"led to a landmark case that led to the Equal Opportunity Act,"},{"time":651000,"text":"and the Violence Against Women Act and others."},{"time":653000,"text":"And then the movie about this person doing these things,"},{"time":656000,"text":"then led to this greater renewal."},{"time":660000,"text":"And so again,"},{"time":661000,"text":"it goes back to betting on good people doing good things."}]},{"cues":[{"time":665000,"text":"Speaking of which, our fellow TEDster, Al --"},{"time":668000,"text":"I first saw Al do his slide show presentation"},{"time":671000,"text":"on global warming in May of 2005."},{"time":675000,"text":"At that point, I thought I knew something about global warming."},{"time":678000,"text":"I thought it was a 30 to 50 year problem."},{"time":680000,"text":"And after we saw his slide show,"},{"time":682000,"text":"it became clear that it was much more urgent."},{"time":685000,"text":"And so right afterwards, I met backstage with Al, and"},{"time":689000,"text":"with Lawrence Bender, who was there, and Laurie David,"},{"time":691000,"text":"and Davis Guggenheim,"},{"time":693000,"text":"who was running documentaries for Participant at the time."},{"time":697000,"text":"And with Al's blessing, we decided on the spot to turn it into a film,"},{"time":701000,"text":"because we felt that we could get the message out there"},{"time":704000,"text":"far more quickly than having Al go around the world,"},{"time":708000,"text":"speaking to audiences of 100 or 200 at a time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":710000,"text":"And you know, there's another adage in Hollywood,"},{"time":713000,"text":"that nobody knows nothing about anything."},{"time":715000,"text":"And I really thought this was going to be"},{"time":717000,"text":"a straight-to-PBS charitable initiative."},{"time":721000,"text":"And so it was a great shock to all of us"},{"time":724000,"text":"when the film really captured the public interest,"},{"time":727000,"text":"and today is mandatory viewing in schools in England and Scotland,"},{"time":731000,"text":"and most of Scandinavia."},{"time":733000,"text":"We've sent 50,000 DVDs to high school teachers in the U.S."},{"time":739000,"text":"and it's really changed the debate on global warming."},{"time":743000,"text":"It was also a pretty good year for this guy."},{"time":745000,"text":"We now call Al the George Clooney of global warming."},{"time":748000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":750000,"text":"And for Participant, this is just the start."},{"time":754000,"text":"Everything we do looks at the major issues in the world."},{"time":756000,"text":"And we have 10 films in production right now,"},{"time":759000,"text":"and dozens others in development."},{"time":762000,"text":"I'll quickly talk about a few coming up."},{"time":764000,"text":"One is \"Charlie Wilson's War,\" with Tom Hanks and Julia Roberts."},{"time":768000,"text":"And it's the true story of Congressman Charlie Wilson, and"},{"time":771000,"text":"how he funded the Taliban to fight the Russians in Afghanistan."},{"time":776000,"text":"And we're also doing a movie called \"The Kite Runner,\""},{"time":778000,"text":"based on the book \"The Kite Runner,\" also about Afghanistan."},{"time":782000,"text":"And we think once people see these films,"},{"time":783000,"text":"they'll have a much better understanding of that part of the world"},{"time":786000,"text":"and the Middle East in general."}]},{"cues":[{"time":788000,"text":"We premiered a film called \"The Chicago 10\" at Sundance this year."},{"time":792000,"text":"It's based on the protesters at the Democratic Convention in 1968,"},{"time":796000,"text":"Abby Hoffman and crew,"},{"time":798000,"text":"and, again, a story about a small group of individuals"},{"time":802000,"text":"who did make change in the world."},{"time":804000,"text":"And a documentary that we're doing on Jimmy Carter"},{"time":808000,"text":"and his Mid-East peace efforts over the years."},{"time":810000,"text":"And in particular, we've been following him on his recent book tour,"},{"time":815000,"text":"which, as many of you know, has been very non-controversial --"},{"time":818000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":819000,"text":"-- which is really bad for getting people to come see a movie."}]},{"cues":[{"time":822000,"text":"In closing, I'd like to say that everybody has the opportunity"},{"time":826000,"text":"to make change in their own way."},{"time":828000,"text":"And all the people in this room"},{"time":831000,"text":"have done so through their business lives,"},{"time":833000,"text":"or their philanthropic work, or their other interests."},{"time":837000,"text":"And one thing that I've learned"},{"time":839000,"text":"is that there's never one right way to make change."},{"time":841000,"text":"One can do it as a tech person, or as a finance person,"},{"time":844000,"text":"or a nonprofit person, or as an entertainment person,"},{"time":848000,"text":"but every one of us is all of those things and more."}]},{"cues":[{"time":852000,"text":"And I believe if we do these things,"},{"time":855000,"text":"we can close the opportunity gaps, we can close the hope gaps."},{"time":859000,"text":"And I can imagine, if we do this,"},{"time":861000,"text":"the headlines in 10 years might read something like these:"},{"time":866000,"text":"\"New AIDS Cases in Africa Fall to Zero,\""},{"time":869000,"text":"\"U.S. Imports its Last Barrel of Oil\" --"},{"time":872000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":874000,"text":"-- \"Israelis and Palestinians Celebrate"},{"time":878000,"text":"10 Years of Peaceful Coexistence.\""},{"time":880000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":883000,"text":"And I like this one, \"Snow Has Returned to Kilimanjaro.\""},{"time":885000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":888000,"text":"And finally, an eBay listing for one well-traveled slide show,"},{"time":894000,"text":"now obsolete, museum piece. Please contact Al Gore."},{"time":900000,"text":"And I believe that, working together,"},{"time":903000,"text":"we can make all of these things happen."},{"time":905000,"text":"And I want to thank you all for having me here today."},{"time":907000,"text":"It's been a real honor. Thank you."},{"time":908000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":911000,"text":"Oh, thank you."}]}]}